snippet.textDisplay:
SPOILER:


I am honestly convinced that Elsa is an animation (or reanimation) of the fifth spirit. Just like how the others were in some sort of form and used to live in the Enchanted Forest like the others. Olaf's "Water has memory" just supports it because in "Into The Unknown" when she uses her powers, it's literally just a shorter version of the whole plot. i.e. going into the mist; seeing her parents as children; the reindeer; the other spirits. So I think when she sings: "Are you out there? Do you know me? Can you feel me? Can you show me?.." and uses her powers, it's just her memories of her life as a spirit. The fifth spirit just reanimated as Iduna and Agnarr's daughter as a reward, but the true queen of Arendelle was always supposted to be Anna.


Thoughts?
